{"reasoning": "We have only $1 and cannot afford any shop items without selling jokers, which would be inefficient. All current jokers are valuable: Scary Face (+30 chips per face card) synergizes with RED deck's many face cards, Crafty Joker (+80 chips on Flush) is strong with RED deck's Hearts/Diamonds making flushes easier, Mad Joker (+10 Mult on Two Pair) synergizes with Two Pair level 3, and Zany Joker (+12 Mult on Three of a Kind) provides another scoring option. Selling any would reduce power for minimal gain.

The High Priestess (Tarot) could give random Planet cards but costs $3 and we'd need to sell a joker, losing half its value. Even Steven (+4 Mult for even ranks) doesn't align with our strategy. Reroll Surplus voucher ($10) and Jumbo Arcana Pack ($6) are too expensive.

Better to proceed to Big Blind with our current strong joker set and hand levels (Flush level 2, Two Pair level 3). We'll earn money from unspent hands after defeating the blind, and can accumulate interest later. We have one joker slot open for future opportunities. Staying flexible is key."}
